fields.Title: WHIRLING F1 / TITUS ALAIN AND EUGENE
fields.Description: Dialogue with Hardie and the surviving boys

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Cunn and what-the-fuck now?" He st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cunn and what-the-fuck now?" He stares at Cuno, scratching his head.

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Right." The man sips on his milk."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right." The man sips on his milk.

fields.Title: You: "(Shake it.) "No need to thank me, j..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Shake it.) "No need to thank me, just doing my job."

fields.Title: You: "(Shake it.) "I superstarred the shi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Shake it.) "I superstarred the shit out of that."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Judging by the sight of you..." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Judging by the sight of you..." He looks at your bandages. "I'd suggest crawling into bed with a bottle of whiskey in one hand and a big tit in the other."

fields.Title: You: ""This is getting dark. Let's talk a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is getting dark. Let's talk about happy stuff."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Hey, hey... fuck you for ruining a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, hey... fuck you for ruining a beautiful idea!"

fields.Title: You: ""Same here, man.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Same here, man."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Spotting you, the bruised man spits..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Spotting you, the bruised man spits into the little bowl next to him.

fields.Title: Empathy: "He really hates the Hardie boys. La..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He really hates the Hardie boys. Laying off speed for a few days hasn't changed that. Titus ignoring him doesn't help either.

fields.Title: You: "(Shake it.) "It was an honour to fi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Shake it.) "It was an honour to fight by your side."

fields.Title: You: "(Don't shake.) "Look, I need to tal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Don't shake.) "Look, I need to talk to you."

fields.Title: You: ""Can you help me get into harbour?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Can you help me get into harbour?"

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Man, getting shot has really squee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Man, getting shot has really squeezed all the *funk* out of you." The guy looks up from his table. "Mark my words, one day we'll look back to this day and remember their courage, not their deaths."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Right..." He takes another sip. "B..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right..." He takes another sip. "But today ain't that day yet, is it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Yeah." He takes a swig from the wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah." He takes a swig from the whiskey bottle. "Had to tell Angus's mum about the *honour* that was bestowed upon his son... she didn't share your optimism, copper. But fine... Fuck it. To each his own."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""'Kind of'?! You tried to pin a mur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "'Kind of'?! You tried to pin a murder on me... on *US*!" For a moment he looks like he's going to hit you. "Why did you do that?!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "There's a lump in his throat when h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a lump in his throat when he thinks of Glen, lying on the plaza mosaic, bleeding.

fields.Title: Cuno: "Cuno keeps silent too."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cuno keeps silent too.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Good point, binoclard." Hardie loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good point, binoclard." Hardie looks at his beer. "We'll keep the vol under 12% tonight."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""There I was, thinking -- where are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There I was, thinking -- where are we gonna find a tin opener large enough for those cans? Then coppo loco shows up and just sets a man on fire."

fields.Title: You: ""It was a tactical manoeuvre. Polic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It was a tactical manoeuvre. Police work. You wouldn't understand."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Hell, you both look like you could..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hell, you both look like you could use some feminine company right now."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And Glen... Glen was my friend. Be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And Glen... Glen was my friend. Best I've ever had. I loved that crazy homo like my own brother." He takes a sip of his beer. "We're all fucked without him, but whaddaya do? This job is shit."

fields.Title: You: ""We are born in to this world to di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We are born in to this world to die, it seems. Maybe there's redemption in that? At least it ends one day."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Don't know, don't care. I'll be gl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't know, don't care. I'll be glad if I never see that fucking woman again."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Those guys are what Cuno calls the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Those guys are what Cuno calls the f*g army," he whispers. "They think they're a big deal around here."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "He didn't like him -- that only mak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He didn't like him -- that only makes it worse.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Thank you for your advice, Eugene...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you for your advice, Eugene. And you too, Alain. I do always appreciate a good use of the expression 'milkers'."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Nah, the harbour is in complete lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nah, the harbour is in complete lockdown. Evrart's orders."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""But Angus..." He gulps. "He was ju..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But Angus..." He gulps. "He was just a stupid kid. Didn't realize the mess he'd gotten into... trusted me... Still, the balls on that kid! Went down fighting for someone else's shit like a fat angry bear."
fields.Alternate1: "But Lizzy and Angus..." He gulps. "They were just stupid kids. Didn't realize the shit they got into before it was too late... I feel responsible for both. For all of them really."

fields.Title: You: ""Frontier justice -- I like it!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Frontier justice -- I like it!"

fields.Title: You: ""What can I say, I'm a wildcard, th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What can I say, I'm a wildcard, that's my method."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I guess what I'm trying to say her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess what I'm trying to say here is, thank you for intervening, fellas -- that was mighty brave of you." He extends his hand.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Seeing you approach, the bruised ma..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seeing you approach, the bruised man clenches his fists.

fields.Title: Logic: "Maybe he has a point there?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe he has a point there?

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "It sincerely amuses him -- how hard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It sincerely amuses him -- how hard these guys typecast themselves.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""We don't have time for that grief..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We don't have time for that grief shit," the kid suddenly interjects. "Cunn and Pig are gunning it. We got a case to solve."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Fuck it, let 'em have their day, Cu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fuck it, let 'em have their day, Cuno thinks. Doesn't have to be a joke. Cuno was just sayin' we need to solve this shit...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Take it easy on the drink. The dan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Take it easy on the drink. The danger has not passed -- this town needs you on your feet."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I will, coppo. That's a promise."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I will, coppo. That's a promise." He puts his can down. "Now scoot, 'cause the Hardie boys got some mourning and drinking to do."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You slimy piece of shit..." He sur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You slimy piece of shit..." He surveys you. "You're lucky you got shot, 'cause I've a mind to tear you to pieces right now, but..."
fields.Alternate1: "You slimy piece of shit..." The big man surveys you. "You're lucky you got shot, 'cause I've a mind to tear you to pieces right now, but..."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Absolutely! Today I'm going to get..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Absolutely! Today I'm going to get drunk, eat good food, and bed a good-looking gal, 'cause tomorrow a motor carriage might run me over..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Fuck off, asshole, can't you see w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck off, asshole, can't you see we're mourning here?!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Dennis? That poor little rat is de..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dennis? That poor little rat is dead too." He shakes his head. "I always thought he'd run. But, no, he stayed. Stupid brave fella."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I'm gonna let it slide on the coun..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm gonna let it slide on the count of all of us stickin' it to these tea pots together, but you need to get your head out of your ass, copper. Or you'll *never* solve this shit."

fields.Title: You: ""Bye, Titus." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Bye, Titus." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Look, I just want to talk...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, I just want to talk..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure, sure." He doesn't seem to mi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, sure." He doesn't seem to mind your rudeness.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Yeah, go pay Monica a visit in Jam..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, go pay Monica a visit in Jamrock. She's got a knack for making men forget about their worries. Biggest pair of milkers in all of Revachol."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure, coppo -- puppies and daisies..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, coppo -- puppies and daisies. Shoot!"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Careful. Looks like we got a situa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Careful. Looks like we got a situation here." He gives you a knowing nod.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "An honest tactic. And effective."
fields.Dialogue Text: An honest tactic. And effective.

fields.Title: You: ""Look, I just need a moment of your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, I just need a moment of your time, and then you don't ever have to see me again."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""*First*, we're gonna find Dennis...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "*First*, we're gonna find Dennis..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant shakes his head but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant shakes his head but doesn't say anything.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Nope.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nope."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You aren't much of a thinker, are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You aren't much of a thinker, are you?" He sticks his giant index finger right in your face.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Well, your method is shit!" He sti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, your method is shit!" He sticks his giant index finger right in your face.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""That was one hell of a shot. Hell..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That was one hell of a shot. Hell of a shot! The fucks *did not* expect that." He looks at you with unmistakable respect.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "The way the last word is emphasized..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The way the last word is emphasized suggests a veiled threat to your person.

fields.Title: You: "(Shake it.) "This was a pillow figh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Shake it.) "This was a pillow fight compared to The Gloaming that is soon at hand. We shall all perish in the coming cleanse."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""We don't. Gonna sit tight, get dru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We don't. Gonna sit tight, get drunk and mourn our fallen comrades till bossman sends word." He shakes his can. "Times are changing, coppo."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""To our fallen comrades!" Titus rai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To our fallen comrades!" Titus raises his whiskey bottle and takes a sip so manly it makes his eyes water.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I guess I'll take a closer look at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess I'll take a closer look at our Union members. There's bound to be some ambitious fellows there who'd love nothing more than advancing social democracy by bustin' some heads."

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on, where's that Shanky-fella?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on, where's that Shanky-fella?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Dennis? You *saw* him run. He's a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dennis? You *saw* him run. He's a mean little shit and I never trusted him." He shakes his head. "He better run real fast now -- *real* fast."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "And Titus Hardie himself would make..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And Titus Hardie himself would make a good officer. That man was born to lead.

fields.Title: You: ""Shouldn't drown your sorrows in bo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Shouldn't drown your sorrows in bottle. It doesn't work, believe me, I've tried."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Impressive shit, copper. None of u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Impressive shit, copper. None of us would be breathing right now if it wasn't for..." He pauses, then extends his hand. "I guess what I'm trying to say here is, thank you."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Well, cheers anyway, copper!" He r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, cheers anyway, copper!" He raises his whiskey bottle in salute.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You look after yourself now, coppe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You look after yourself now, copper," he says with a warm smile. "Death passed on you today, but men don't get that lucky twice."
fields.Alternate1: "Take care, coppers," he says with a warm smile. "You two look after yourselves now. Death passed on you today, but men don't get that lucky twice."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And if you ever feel like the unif..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And if you ever feel like the uniform is holding you back... I've got a few vacancies. You'd make one hard Hardie boy, copper."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm sorry about the people you los..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry about the people you lost."

fields.Title: Alain: ""*I'm* going to find Dennis," he in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*I'm* going to find Dennis," he interjects. "I'm going to find him and then I'm going to kill him."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Mhm," he nods without really liste..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm," he nods without really listening. "We're hunting that rat down -- let it be known what happens to cowards. And then..." He thinks for a moment.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Go ahead then. Maybe they'll only b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Go ahead then. Maybe they'll only break his legs.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "His hand is covered in bruises and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His hand is covered in bruises and half-plastered. Still, this hulking lump of man is glad to be alive.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Dick Mullen on steroids..." A sad..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dick Mullen on steroids..." A sad smile passes over his bruised face. "Glen would have liked you had he gotten to... never mind."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Or go pay your partner a visit in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Or go pay your partner a visit in the hospital. I hear he got shot up pretty bad."

fields.Title: You: ""They were good people. I'm sorry i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They were good people. I'm sorry it went like that."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Easy now, Al. His buddy got busted..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Easy now, Al. His buddy got busted up pretty bad too. If that's his way of dealing with it, I say let him have it."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Or you might die of a heart failur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Or you might die of a heart failure... Or syphilis?"

fields.Title: You: ""I panicked, alright?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I panicked, alright?"

fields.Title: Drama: "He did."
fields.Dialogue Text: He did.

fields.Title: Composure: "His clenched jaw says otherwise. If..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His clenched jaw says otherwise. If anything, it's another score for him to settle. One day -- it'll have to wait for now.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Might even ask Tibbs if he's tired..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Might even ask Tibbs if he's tired of replacing windows and maybe wants to have some fun with his brother." He pauses. "Anyway, don't you worry -- as long as Titus Hardie's standing, there *will* be Hardie boys."

fields.Title: You: ""Titus, after all we've been throug..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Titus, after all we've been through, level with me... you really liked her, didn't you?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""No, it isn't fuckin' *alright*!" H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, it isn't fuckin' *alright*!" He is breathing heavily as he sticks his giant index finger right in your face.

fields.Title: You: ""The RCM could really use a man lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The RCM could really use a man like you, Titus. Think about it."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Crazy motherfucker..." He lets out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Crazy motherfucker..." He lets out a whistle. "Didn't think you had that fury in you, but I guess I've misjudged a lot of people lately..."
fields.Alternate1: "Crazy motherfuckers..." The big man lets out a whistle. "Didn't think you had that fury in you, but I guess I've misjudged a lot of people lately..."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Get out of here, punk! Can't you s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Get out of here, punk! Can't you see we're honouring our dead here."

fields.Title: You: "Shake his hand and nod in silence."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shake his hand and nod in silence.

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know what happened to Klaas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know what happened to Klaasje?"

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, how do *you* get in, then?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, how do *you* get in, then?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Hey, it's you again!" He smiles, m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, it's you again!" He smiles, more than a bit drunk now. "I've been thinking about it and you know what... we're both cops. This city is big enough for two cops."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""You killed half the town," he whis..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You killed half the town," he whispers. "Remember?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Take care, copper!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Take care, copper!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Okay, Mr. Sunshine... I guess I'd..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, Mr. Sunshine... I guess I'd be pretty gloomy too had I gotten shot in the ass." He shakes your hand and smiles.

fields.Title: You: ""Listen, about me kind of throwing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen, about me kind of throwing you under the wagon there..."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not sure that really applies h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not sure that really applies here..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I guess what I'm trying to say her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess what I'm trying to say here is, thank you for intervening, coppo -- that was mighty brave of you." He extends his hand.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""God, why are you still here..." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "God, why are you still here..." He's getting quite drunk now. "I'm sick of seeing you cops around."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Okay..." He looks at the lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay..." He looks at the lieutenant. "Three cops. Me, you, and your little friend here."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Seeing you approach the bruised man..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seeing you approach the bruised man raises his beer in welcome.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""You're welcome, binoclard," Titus'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're welcome, binoclard," Titus' response is completely unironic. "You're all right in my book."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Look, fellows," he points at you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, fellows," he points at you. "It's Little Miss Pacifist... It's mighty easy when you let others do the fighting for you, isn't it?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Now, how can I help you?" His grip..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Now, how can I help you?" His grip is strong and friendly.

fields.Title: You: ""They died fighting for something t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They died fighting for something they believed in. There's honour in that."

fields.Title: You: ""That's not going to bring back...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's not going to bring back..."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "*Memento mori* or 'remember that yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Memento mori* or 'remember that you must die' is a slogan various religious orders have thrown around since the dawn of mankind, to emphasize the vanity of earthly life and the transient nature of all earthly pursuits. In essence it means one should live virtuously in this life to live better in the afterlife.

fields.Title: Authority: "He's so proud of himself, you're te..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's so proud of himself, you're tempted to believe that *he* just defused the situation.

fields.Title: Suggestion: "Even after all that hell he's still..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even after all that hell he's still bitter about her?

fields.Title: You: ""What's going to happen to the Hard..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's going to happen to the Hardie boys now?"

fields.Title: You: ""Any idea what I should do now?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Any idea what I should do now?"

fields.Title: You: ""So long, fellows. Be good so I don..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So long, fellows. Be good so I don't have to come back here again." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Sure it does." He nods confidently..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure it does." He nods confidently and raises his whiskey bottle. "Live every day like it's your last, 'cause you might be dead tomorrow."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Situation defused," he declares wi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Situation defused," he declares with undue authority.

fields.Title: Authority: "This is big. It's as big of a thank..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is big. It's as big of a thank-you as Titus Hardie can muster under *any* circumstances.

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on, what about that Shanky-fe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on, what about that Shanky-fella?"

fields.Title: You: ""My condolences for your lost frien..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My condolences for your lost friends."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I applaud the initiative, even tho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I applaud the initiative, even though *you* can't shoot for shit, officer." He rubs his neck. "Still, that moment of confusion might just be the reason we are still standing here..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I think it's about time you get th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think it's about time you get the fuck out of Martinaise, don't you agree *copper*?"

fields.Title: You: ""Fine, I'm leaving." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine, I'm leaving." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He shrugs and tries to look uninter..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He shrugs and tries to look uninterested.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He nods and takes another sip of wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods and takes another sip of whiskey.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""And I was wrong about your big dic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And I was wrong about your big dick too... you don't have a big dick." He stares disappointed into his beer.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "He gives you a quick two-finger sal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He gives you a quick two-finger salute.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""In the light of your..." he search..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In the light of your..." he searches for the right word, then finds it, "badassery... I'm even willing to forgive the fact you tried to pin a murder on us."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Oh, I understand alright..." he sa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, I understand alright..." he says with a disgusted grimace. "Just say your bit and get out of our booth, asshole."

fields.Title: Alain: ""Coppo loco." He looks at you and n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Coppo loco." He looks at you and nods. "Good luck in Jamrock. Scars make the best tattoos, they say."
fields.Alternate1: He nods to you and then to the lieutenant. "Coppo loco... and the, uh, normal cop, I guess. Good luck in Jamrock. Scars make the best tattoos, they say."

fields.Title: Eugene: ""Thanks for getting involved, man...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thanks for getting involved, man. Not a lot of cops would step in that line of fire, but you did."
fields.Alternate1: "Thanks for getting involved, guys. Not a lot of cops would step in that line of fire, but you did."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "The tone of the statement is so mat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tone of the statement is so matter-of-fact, it's as though he were talking about picking up a morning newspaper on his daily walk around the block.

fields.Title: You: ""What does that mean?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What does that mean?"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""It means you might die tomorrow, s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It means you might die tomorrow, so live every day like it's your last. Ain't that right, fellows?"

fields.Title: You: ""I analysed the evidence and it poi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I analysed the evidence and it pointed to you. Nothing personal."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I guess what I'm trying to say her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess what I'm trying to say here is, thank you for intervening, coppo -- that was mighty brave of you." He extends his hand.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Here it comes. The last one is the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Here it comes. The last one is the worst one. He only deals with it by drinking copious amounts of 8% beer.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""MOTHERFUCKER!!!" His roar almost r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "MOTHERFUCKER!!!" His roar almost ruptures your eardrums. "You tried to pin a murder on us! What more do you think we have to talk about?!"

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Fine," he grunts. "Talk.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine," he grunts. "Talk."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Likewise, copper. Likewise." His g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Likewise, copper. Likewise." His grip is strong and friendly.

fields.Title: Alain: ""Ah, cut that shit out," the Mesque..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, cut that shit out," the Mesque interjects angrily. "That's the kind of rhetoric bangers tell to kids in Jamrock to get them to join a gang. I'm sick and tired of this honour bullshit!"

fields.Title: You: ""Your guy, your responsibility -- d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Your guy, your responsibility -- do what you feel is right."

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah... uh... totally, totally.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah... uh... totally, totally."

fields.Title: You: ""Look, I'm very sorry. I shouldn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, I'm very sorry. I shouldn't have done that. Please forgive me."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Titus' hand is covered in bruises a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Titus' hand is covered in bruises and half-plastered. Still, this hulking lump of man is glad to be alive.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Titus makes no attempt to hide his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Titus makes no attempt to hide his disgust. Grief-stricken anger boils in him.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "He did *not* appreciate you blaming..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He did *not* appreciate you blaming him for the murder -- but then again you probably saved his ass later, so he says...

fields.Title: You: ""Actually, I just came to say goodb..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually, I just came to say goodbye." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, got it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, got it."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "Titus nods. "What else?""
fields.Dialogue Text: Titus nods. "What else?"

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, got it.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, got it."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I guess what I'm trying to say her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess what I'm trying to say here is, thank you for intervening, fellas -- that was mighty brave of you." He extends his hand.

fields.Title: Logic: "He's right. The numbers are replace..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's right. The numbers are replaceable. In an organization of thousands of men, there are plenty who'd join.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Easy E, let the kid be. This is a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Easy E, let the kid be. This is a day of mourning and I don't want it turned into a joke... you chasing the kid around, the kid calling you a f******t. We don't need that shit."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""I mean, you pitch like a blind har..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mean, you pitch like a blind harlequin on speed, but that moment of confusion might just be the reason we are still standing here..."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: "His bruised face stiffens. "Theo wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His bruised face stiffens. "Theo was old. I think he'd be pretty happy with the way he went. Never could imagine him withering away on a sickbed."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Well yeah... *memento mori*, right?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well yeah... *memento mori*, right?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant sighs."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant sighs.
